                <h2 class="green><u>Welcome to Milo's Website!</u></h2>
                <p>Hi everyone, my name is Milo! I’m a 2 year old English Labrador from Long Island, New York. Here you can find all you need to know about the English Labrador breed. From our <em>favorite snacks</em> and <em>training tips</em>, to our <em>temperament</em> and <em>personality traits</em>. Here, you can learn if adopting an English Labrador would be the right fit for you and your family, and I’ll be your guide!                </p>
            </section>
            <section id="history">
                <h2 class="green"><u>History of the English Labrador</u></h2>
                <p>Way back in the <strong>1800s,</strong> my Labrador ancestors were hardworking fishing dogs in Newfoundland. They helped to reel in nets, swim through cold water, and fetch about anything. Some of us traveled over to England where breeders shaped us into the English Labs you see today. Now, we’re a little stockier, calmer, and always ready for a piece of food to drop. We’ve always been loyal hunters, helpers, and cuddle buddies, the true man’s best friend!</p>
            </section>

            <article id="temperament">
                <h2 class="green"><u>Temperament: Gentle, Loving, Loyal</u></h2>
                <p>English Labs are known for their calm, yet energetic, temperament, stocky builds, and loyal nature. We are affectionate, playful, and thrive in a family who gives us attention, love, and <strong>lots</strong> of tennis balls. We are great with kids and love making new friends; we’re basically big walking teddy bears.</p>
            </article>
